      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LILLY LOTUS (5) has been racing at Melton so far this campaign where she recorded a fresh second three back. Looks suited returning to a circuit and distance where she has recorded a win and two placings in three attempts and will be at peak fitness now so can show her best. YUKON BE SERIOUS NZ (1) produced an encouraging effort to come from a wide draw for fourth when resuming at Menangle last week. Fitter for that and is well served by the ace draw. HITCH TO HIS STAR (7) has been racing at Shepparton of late where he recorded a win two back. Draws wide but will enjoy the return to a venue where he is unbeaten in three appearances and he also goes very well at this distance, winning five from seven. MIKI LOCH (4) must be considered off some good form here, finishing runner-up a week ago and winning over this distance three back.",
